Day - 24
--------

XPath
-----

XPath is an address of the element.

DOM - Document Object Model

2 types of xpath
-----------------

1) Absolute xpath(full xpath)

	Ex: /html/body/header/div/div/div[2]/div/input

2) Relative xpath(partial xpath)

	Ex: //*[@id="search"]/input
	
	Which xpath will be preferred?
	Relative xpath
	
	
	Differences between Absolute xpath and Relative xpath
	------------------------------------------------------
	
	1) Absolute xpath starts with /     --> Represent root node
	   Relative xpath starts with //    
	   
	2) Absolute xpath do not use attributes
	   Relative xpath works with attributes
	   
	3) Absolute xpath traverse through each node till it find element
	   Relative xpath directly jump and find the element by using attribute
	   
	   
	Relative xpath
	--------------
	1) Automatically - Devtools, Selectorhub
	2) Manually(own xpath)
	
	syntax: 
	------
	
	//tagname[@attribute='value']
	//*[@attribute='value']
			
	//img[@title='MacBook']
	
	XPath with single attribute
	---------------------------
	driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[@placeholder='Search']")).sendKeys("T-shirts");
	
	
	XPath with multiple attribute
	-----------------------------
	//input[@name='search'][@placeholder='Search']
	
	xpath with 'and' 'or' operator
	------------------------------
	//input[@name='search' and @placeholder='Search']
	//input[@name='search' or @placeholder='Search']
	
	
	xpath with inner text - text()
	------------------------------
	//a[text()='Desktops']
	//a[text()='MacBook']
	
	
	<a href="https://xyz.com"> Click Me</a>
	linktext = yes
	inner text = yes
	
	<div> Welcome </div>
	link text = no
	inner text = yes
	
	
	xpath with contains()
	---------------------
	//input[contains(@placeholder,'Sea')]
	
	
	xpath with start-with()
	-----------------------
	//input[start-with(@placeholder,'Sea')]
	
	
	Handling dynamic attributes
	---------------------------
	//*[@id='start' or @id='stop']
	//*[contains(@id,'st')]
	//*[starts-with(@id, 'st')]
	
	if name=xyz001  xyz002  xyz003   xyz004
	//*[contains(@name, 'xyz')]
	//*[contains(@name, '00']
	//*[starts-with(@name, 'xyz']
	
	
	if name=001xyz  002xyz   003xyz   001xyz
	//*[contains(@name, 'xyz')]
	//*[starts-with(@name, '00')]
	
	if name=101xyz  201xyz  301xyz  401xyz
	//*[contains(@name, 'xyz')]
	
	
	chained xpath
	-------------
	//div[@id='logo']/a/img
	
	
	Locating Parent Element
	-----------------------
	<form...
		<div
		<div
			<input id="txtUsername"
			<span
		</div
		
		self node input
		//input[@id='txtUsername']/parent::form
		//input[@id='txtUsername']/parent::*
		//input[@id='txtUsername']/..
		
	Locating a child element
	------------------------
	<div id="divUsername"
			<input id="txtUsername"
			<span
	</div
	
	//div[@id='divUsername']/child::input
	//div[@id='divUsername']/input
	
	
	Locating ancestors of a known element
	-------------------------------------
	<form...
		<div
		<div
			<input id="txtUsername"
			<span
		</div
		
		self node input
		
		//input[@id='txtUsername']/ancestor::form
		//input[@id='txtUsername']/ancestor::*
		
	Locating descendant of a known element
	--------------------------------------
	 <form id="frmLogin"
		<div
		<div
			<input id="txtUsername"
			<span
		</div
		
		self node form
		//form[@id='frmLogin']/descendant::input
		//form[@id='frmLogin']/descendant::span
		
		//form[@id='frmLogin']//input
		
		
		<div
			<div
				<div
				<div
				<div
				
		div/div/div[3]
		
